<bdy>

The <b>junction tree algorithm</b> is a method used in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../488/233488.xml">
machine learning</link> for <link>
exact marginalization</link> in general <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../806/325806.xml">
graph</link>s.  In essence, it entails performing <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../010/800010.xml">
belief propagation</link> on a modified graph called a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../023/159023.xml">
junction tree</link>. The basic premise is to eliminate <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../609/168609.xml">
cycle</link>s by clustering them into single nodes.
